  "prompt": "What does \"AAA\" mean in AAA title game?",
  "response": "In the context of video games, \"AAA\" (pronounced \"triple-A\") refers to games that are produced by major industry publishers and typically have the largest budgets, extensive marketing campaigns, and high production values. These games often feature top-tier graphics, sound, and gameplay design, and they are generally developed by large teams of skilled professionals. AAA titles are expected to achieve high levels of commercial success and are often among the most well-known and widely played games in the market. Examples of AAA games include titles like \"The Last of Us Part II,\" \"Call of Duty,\" and \"Assassin's Creed.\"",
